00:34:32.760 --> 00:34:34.909
And I'm trying to move us into
the digital age and get away

00:34:34.909 --> 00:34:36.360
from the paper aspect.

00:34:36.360 --> 00:34:38.750
But traditionally, there's been
a challenge there where

00:34:38.750 --> 00:34:41.900
testing on the computer is seen
as being very different

00:34:41.900 --> 00:34:44.150
from testing on paper.

00:34:44.150 --> 00:34:46.679
Based on your experience, do you
see that continuing to be

00:34:46.679 --> 00:34:49.820
an issue with the generations
that are coming up with the

00:34:49.820 --> 00:34:51.749
computers and the tablets
the same way it

00:34:51.749 --> 00:34:52.610
has been in the past?

00:34:52.610 --> 00:34:57.610
Or do you have any words
on that issue?

00:34:57.610 --> 00:34:58.420
PETER NORVIG: So that's
a good point.

00:34:58.420 --> 00:35:02.650
I mean, I think you want
to be fair to everyone.

00:35:02.650 --> 00:35:06.810
You don't want to disadvantage
someone by saying you have to

00:35:06.810 --> 00:35:09.060
take this test using technology
that you're not

00:35:09.060 --> 00:35:10.870
familiar with.

00:35:10.870 --> 00:35:14.290
But I think the technology that
we're also already using

00:35:14.290 --> 00:35:17.180
of filling in little bubbles
on a piece of paper, that's

00:35:17.180 --> 00:35:19.590
not a very natural thing
for people to do.

00:35:19.590 --> 00:35:21.920
That's something that
you had to learn.

00:35:21.920 --> 00:35:25.030
And so I think replacing that
with learning to use a

00:35:25.030 --> 00:35:28.810
computer is fine, as long as
everybody has access to

00:35:28.810 --> 00:35:32.280
training for it and it's not
you're ruled out because

00:35:32.280 --> 00:35:35.380
you've never seen
a mouse before.

00:35:35.380 --> 00:35:39.630
I think maybe tablets have a
smaller learning curve and so

00:35:39.630 --> 00:35:42.820
that mitigates that
to some degree.

00:35:42.820 --> 00:35:47.525
And you'll just start to see
more and more kids growing up

00:35:47.525 --> 00:35:49.320
and being more familiar
with the technology.

00:35:49.320 --> 00:35:52.990
And they'll think it's odd to
be using paper and pencil

00:35:52.990 --> 00:35:55.380
rather than using computers.

00:35:55.380 --> 00:35:58.460
AUDIENCE: Hi, my name is
