00:36:56.710 --> 00:37:00.540
That in a college class, we're
able to break up the world

00:37:00.540 --> 00:37:03.510
into curricula in a more
well-defined way.

00:37:03.510 --> 00:37:07.810
Whereas, for younger kids, I
think you expressed it well.

00:37:07.810 --> 00:37:10.270
That there's lots of directions
that they could go

00:37:10.270 --> 00:37:13.510
in and it's not that every kid
has to follow the same path.

00:37:13.510 --> 00:37:16.410
And that's part of the reason
why I want to have the tools

00:37:16.410 --> 00:37:17.600
to be able to build
up this stuff.

00:37:17.600 --> 00:37:23.440
I think it would be a shame to
show a kid use this online

00:37:23.440 --> 00:37:25.490
tool and there's only one
linear path through it.

00:37:25.490 --> 00:37:27.650
And every kid has to follow
the same path.

00:37:27.650 --> 00:37:29.370
I think that doesn't
make sense.

00:37:29.370 --> 00:37:31.690
Maybe it makes sense for
differential geometry, but it

00:37:31.690 --> 00:37:33.480
doesn't make sense for a kid.

00:37:33.480 --> 00:37:35.780
And so if you want to give them
that, it's got to be more

00:37:35.780 --> 00:37:38.060
you're giving them a playground
