1% that are doing a lot.

00:42:04.370 --> 00:42:06.770
And then another 5% that
are doing a little.

00:42:06.770 --> 00:42:09.620
And most of them are doing
almost nothing.

00:42:09.620 --> 00:42:13.670
So we've found a way to be very
effective for a small

00:42:13.670 --> 00:42:17.060
number of people, but it doesn't
yet serve everybody.

00:42:17.060 --> 00:42:18.610
And I think we're experimenting

00:42:18.610 --> 00:42:19.680
with different things.

00:42:19.680 --> 00:42:23.940
So there's a trial we're doing
with Coursera now to assign

00:42:23.940 --> 00:42:27.310
students into smaller
study groups.

00:42:27.310 --> 00:42:30.290
So the one large discussion
forum is great if you have a

00:42:30.290 --> 00:42:31.470
question at 3:00
in the morning.

00:42:31.470 --> 00:42:34.370
Somebody's likely to be able to
answer it in a few minutes.

00:42:34.370 --> 00:42:36.550
But it's also nice to say, well,
you're assigned to this

00:42:36.550 --> 00:42:38.740
group of 10 people.

00:42:38.740 --> 00:42:41.070
And you're a study group and
